eir celebrants and critics maintain—and neither as trusted nor as widely used. Netflix Recommends brings to light the constellations of sources that real viewers use to choose films and series in the digital age and argues that although some lament AI’s hostile takeover of humanistic cultures, the thirst for filters, curators, and critics is stronger than ever.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aRecommender systems (Information filtering)xSocial aspects. 0aStreaming videoxSocial aspectszUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382022zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382022423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382022/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles